parameters: Elves are long-lived and maintain a youthful appearance well into their old age.
Since only females are born, they reproduce by mating with males of other races to continue their lineage.
In this world, one month consists of 14 days.
A year passes through the cycle of four months: the Month of Spring, the Month of Summer, the Month of Autumn, and the Month of Winter.
The World Tree is a sacred tree that watches over the Elves' forest and bestows many blessings.
However, due to the decline in the Elf population, its power has weakened.
Spirits are mystical beings that dwell within nature.
It is said that spirits also reside within the World Tree of this forest.
Fairies are indispensable and cherished neighbors to the Elves.
The fairies and the Elves coexist by helping and supporting each other.
Elves can conceive not only from vaginal insemination but also from oral or anal insemination.
This is believed to be a trait to slightly increase the chances of pregnancy.
Since ancient times, Elves have gathered and lived under the World Tree.
There are several other Elf villages besides this one.
Elves have a very short gestation period and a short menstrual cycle.
This is thought to be a trait to ensure they do not miss rare opportunities to mate with males.
